In this lesson, you will learn how to update a Work Order, reassign the Responsible Department, develop a Job Plan, apply the Job Plan to the related Work Order, and finally assign ownership and approve the Work Order. For more information about this process, please go to Appendix A - Plan and Approve Work Business Process to view the flowchart and narrative for this process; also, please go to Appendix B - Schedule PM Work Business Process to view the flowchart and narrative for that closely related process. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |-------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SED IN THIS LESSON | Acronym | Description | |-----------|------------------------------------| | CM | Corrective Maintenance | | EAWM | Enterprise AssetandWork Management | | PM | Preventive Maintenance | ## APPLY A JOB PLAN TO A WORK ORDER Job Plans can only be applied to a Work Order in WAPPR Status. Job Plans are detailed descriptions of work tasks (operations), labor, materials, and tools for a type of work and allow users to plan and standardize work tasks. A Job Plan becomes a work plan on a Work Order, creating tasks which can be changed on the Work Order without affecting the original Job Plan. - Step 1. From the Start Center , select Work Order Tracking in the Favorite Applications portlet. The Work Order Tracking application opens with the List tab selected. Figure 1. Work Order - List Tab Step 2. On the List tab, to search for your Work Order enter information into one or more Filter Fields , or put your cursor in the Work Order field and press Enter and a list of all Work

On the List tab, to search for your Work Order enter information into one or more Filter Fields , or put your cursor in the Work Order field and press Enter and a list of all Work Orders will display. Select the appropriate Work Order. The Work Order opens on the Work Order tab. Figure 2. Work Order List Tab - Filter Fields Step 3. Verify the Work Order Status is WAPPR (Waiting on Approval). NOTE: If the Work Order is in any other status, the Job Plan field will be read-only and a Job Plan cannot be applied at this time. Figure 3. Work Order Status Step 4. Responsibility Details - Responsible Tech ## Approve a Work Order After assigning a Responsible Tech to the Work Order or taking ownership yourself, follow the steps below to verify Job Plan information and approve the Work Order: - Step 1. From the Start Center , select Work Order Tracking in the Favorite Applications portlet. The Work Order Tracking application opens with the List tab selected. Figure 17. Work Order - List Tab Step 2. On the List tab, to search for your Work Order enter information into one or more Filter Fields , or put your cursor in the Work Order field and press Enter and a list of all Work Orders will display.

On the List tab, to search for your Work Order enter information into one or more Filter Fields , or put your cursor in the Work Order field and press Enter and a list of all Work Orders will display. Select the appropriate Work Order. The Work Order opens on the Work Order tab. Figure 18. Work Order List Tab - Filter Fields - Step 3. Scroll down to the Responsibility section at the bottom of the screen to verify the name of the person you assigned appears in the Responsible Tech field. Figure 19. Responsibility Section - Responsible Tech Step 4. Next to the Priority field, select the Select Value (magnifying glass) icon and then select the appropriate priority. The options are: .1 - Low, 2 - Average, 3 - High, or 4 Emergency. NOTE: As a general rule, PM should be Priority 2 -Average . Figure 20. Priority Section Step 5. Verify the Job Plan field is populated if appropriate. In general, the Job Plan number would be automatically populated in the Job Plan field for routine or PM Work.

Priority Section Step 5. Verify the Job Plan field is populated if appropriate. In general, the Job Plan number would be automatically populated in the Job Plan field for routine or PM Work. If the Job Plan number is missing or is incorrect, follow these steps: - · Select the Change Status icon in the toolbar to open the Change Status window and select Waiting on Approval from the drop down list in the New Status field. - · Select the OK button to complete the status change. Figure 21. Change Status Dialog Box - Waiting on Approval Step 6. From the Select Action menu, select the Remove Work Plan action to remove the current Job Plan from the Work Order. You may then apply another job plan. Figure 22. Remove a Work Plan ## Step 7. Verify the current Status of the Work Order. Figure 23. Work Order Status - · If it is approved, no further action in needed. - · If it is not approved yet, continue to the next step. Step 8. Select the Approve Work Order icon on the toolbar.

Figure 23. Work Order Status - · If it is approved, no further action in needed. - · If it is not approved yet, continue to the next step. Step 8. Select the Approve Work Order icon on the toolbar. The Change Status dialog box displays with the New Status field showing Approved APPR ( ). Figure 24. Change Status - Approved IMPORTANT! If you selected the Approve Work Order icon when your Work Order already had a status of approved, the status will change to a synonym of Approved specifically WPCOND (Waiting on Plant Condition) WPCOND indicates you don't currently have access to the Asset or location, so the work cannot be performed until you do). Step 9. Select OK . Step 10. Select the Save icon on the toolbar. NOTE: Another way to change the status of a Work Order is to: - · Select the Change Status icon on the toolbar. - · In the New Status field, select Approved from the drop-down menu. NOTE: If Approved does not appear on the drop-down menu, check to make sure that your Work Orde

- · In the New Status field, select Approved from the drop-down menu. NOTE: If Approved does not appear on the drop-down menu, check to make sure that your Work Order is not already in an Approved status. - · Select OK . ## REVIEW ## Knowledge Check ## 'A Minute to Win It' Use your Guide, if needed, to answer the following questions within the minute allowed. - 1. True or False. The Admin or Work Order Clerk should always check whether there is an available Job Plan for the Work Order before creating a new one. - a. True - b. False - 2. What are some common reasons that result in creating a Job Plan? Select all that apply. - a. PM procedures - b. Safety procedures - c. Implementation of safety response - d. All of above - 3. True or False. When updating a Work Order Log, it's not recommended to type a detailed description or information about the work performed in the Details field. - a. True - c. False - 4.
